node.accessibility_caption: Photo by iOSNAM on September 14, 2021. May be an image of phone.

node.text:
The iPhone 13 Pro and iPhone 13 Pro Max.
Featuring a smaller notch, the A15 Bionic chip, an improved camera system, Cinematic mode, 120Hz ProMotion display, a longer battery life, and new colors. More information on apple.com.

𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗔𝘃𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆
The iPhone 13 Pro starts at $999 (US), and the iPhone 13 Pro Max at $1099 (US). Pre-orders begin Friday, September 17, with availability beginning Friday, September 24.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by iOSNAM on September 14, 2021. May be an image of phone.

node.text:
The iPhone 13 and iPhone 13 mini.
Featuring a smaller notch, the A15 Bionic chip, a new dual-camera system for improved photos and videos in low light, Cinematic mode, a longer battery life, and new colors. More information on apple.com.

𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗔𝘃𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆
The iPhone 13 starts at $799 (US), and the iPhone 13 mini at $699 (US). Pre-orders begin Friday, September 17, with availability beginning Friday, September 24.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by iOSNAM on September 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, wrist watch and text.

node.text:
The Apple Watch Series 7.
Featuring a bigger screen, thinner borders, faster charging, dust resistance, and new aluminum case colors. More information on apple.com.

𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗔𝘃𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆
The Apple Watch Series 7 starts at $399 (US) and will be available later this fall.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by iOSNAM on September 14, 2021. May be an image of phone, screen and text.

node.text:
The new iPad mini.
Featuring a new design, the A15 Bionic chip, improved cameras including Center Stage, an USB-C port, 5G, and support for the second generation Apple Pencil. More information on apple.com.

𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗔𝘃𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆
The new iPad mini starts at $499 (US). It is available to order beginning today, and will be in stores beginning Friday, September 24.

node.text:
iOS 14.8 vs iOS 14.7.1
🔋 𝗕𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝗹𝗶𝗳𝗲: decreased with 0.43%, so almost no changes in battery life.
⏱ 𝗣𝗲𝗿𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲: increased with 0.23%, so almost no changes in performance.
These results are averages, so they may vary on each device.

#ioscompared

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by iOSNAM on September 07, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text.

node.text:
Official — Apple has officially announced its September event! The event with tagline “California streaming.” will take place on Tuesday September 14 at 10 a.m. PDT. The event will be completely virtual for the second year in a row.

During this event, Apple will likely announce the iPhone 13 and the Apple Watch Series 7. Other possible announcements include the AirPods 3, a new iPad mini, and a new entry-level iPad.
